$Id: README,v 1.1 2009/02/17 14:05:27 oxon Exp $
PyCRFlux is a python package that has some useful utilities to plot CR fluxes
and calculate diffuse gamma-ray flux.

=== Developers ===

- Akira Okumura oxon@ceres.phys.s.u-tokyo.ac.jp

=== Requirements ===

- Python 2.5 (other version is not tested)
  http://www.python.org/
- ROOT and PyROOT (tested with only version 5.22.00)
  http://root.cern.ch/
- numpy
  http://numpy.scipy.org/
- pyfits
  http://www.stsci.edu/resources/software_hardware/pyfits
- cparamlib 2.1.0 and modified ParamModel.py
  http://www.slac.stanford.edu/~niklas/cparamlib/index.html
- FORTRAN compiler g77/gfortran/ifort etc.

=== Getting Started ===

- Installation
$ tar zxvf PyCRFlux-x.y.z.tar.gz
$ cd PyCRFlux-x.y.z
$ python setup.py install

- Test
Run the scripts in "test" directory

- Write Your Code
See the scripts in "examples" directory

